    "body": "## Problem\n\nNo way for the default autocmd for Progress to show indeterminate progress.\n\n## Solution\n\nDistinguish 0 an omitted progress percent, and treat omitted percent as indeterminate progress bar.\nAdditionally, statusline percent now shows 0% when previously it was omitted.\n\n## Screenshots\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d27ff6fa-1351-43d8-b95f-79326523ca1c",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">Treat percent either as 0 or unset as indeterminate.\r\n\r\nIs this what applications actually do? I wouldn't expect 0 to have this behavior. `0` is 0%, not indeterminate. Interpreting `percent == nil` as \"indeterminate\" makes sense though.",
